    <text>
        <body>
            <head>21. Notes of a <orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">National Security
                    Council</orgName> Meeting<note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d21fn1"
                    >Source: <orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">National Security
                        Council</orgName>, National Security Council Institutional Files, Box
                    SR—101, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"><orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma"
                            >NSC</orgName></gloss> 49A. Secret. Drafted by Wheeler. The original
                    text is handwritten. Brackets and ellipses are in the original text. The editor
                    transcribed the portion of the text here specifically for this volume. An image
                    of the notes is Appendix B. According to <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq"
                        >the President</persName>’s Daily Diary, the meeting took place in the
                    Cabinet Room and ended at approximately 10:45 a.m. No formal minutes of this
                    meeting were found.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1982-05-21T09:43:00-04:00">May 21, 1982, 9:43 a.m.</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p><persName corresp="rec2p5eZ5kgeXCRJ4">Bud McF</persName>: review earlier
                decision—here today to cover 5 remaining agenda items—(1) interim restraints
                (substantive &amp; public affairs context—to ratify <gloss target="#t_SALT_1"><rs
                        corresp="rec6OIA4luUvtBKNn" type="event">SALT</rs></gloss>
                <rs corresp="recF3SBVeQQW0d1aM" type="agreement-or-mandate">II</rs> would legitimize
                buildup, legitimize gross inequalities, delay getting on w/reductions—review pros
                &amp; cons—any comments? [no]</p>
            <p><persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Pres</persName>: what’s good, if anything, in
                    <gloss target="#t_SALT_1"><rs corresp="rec6OIA4luUvtBKNn" type="event"
                    >SALT</rs></gloss>
                <rs corresp="recF3SBVeQQW0d1aM" type="agreement-or-mandate">II</rs>?</p>
            <p><persName corresp="rec2p5eZ5kgeXCRJ4">Bud</persName>: counting rules</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="receeGTv8IaT6tukJ">Haig</persName>: preclude breakout they could
                do—we’re <hi rendition="simple_italic">not</hi> abiding by <gloss target="#t_SALT_1"
                        ><rs corresp="rec6OIA4luUvtBKNn" type="event">SALT</rs></gloss>
                <rs corresp="recF3SBVeQQW0d1aM" type="agreement-or-mandate">II</rs> per se—political
                element</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recDfVAWTlyHCzJgS">Meese</persName>: strategic planning not
                constrained</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recg0WDsRQgtuIKMw">Weinberger</persName>: densepack/<gloss
                    target="#t_ALCM_1"><rs corresp="rec3r8I0hO6jAW3Fm" type="topic"
                    >ALCM</rs></gloss>—I don’t think the Soviets could do more than they’ve done
                now—if we say we’ll abide by <gloss target="#t_SALT_1"><rs
                        corresp="rec6OIA4luUvtBKNn" type="event">SALT</rs></gloss>
                <rs corresp="recF3SBVeQQW0d1aM" type="agreement-or-mandate">II</rs>, I don’t think
                we’ll get on with <gloss target="#t_START_1"><rs corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O"
                        type="event">START</rs></gloss>
            </p>
            <p><persName corresp="recDfVAWTlyHCzJgS">Meese</persName>: I was assuming that what the
                    <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Pres</persName>. said earlier—we’ll not be
                constrained in planning</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recM8U5HOaBRfTDmg">Rostow</persName>: for the moment, it’s in our
                interest to abide—no advantage to change policy—<gloss target="#t_SFRC_1"><orgName
                        corresp="reclsFHhOHbKFFN2I">SFRC</orgName></gloss>
            </p>
            <p><persName corresp="recg0WDsRQgtuIKMw">Weinberger</persName>: I’m not advocating
                public announcement—we need to be clear internally</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recDfVAWTlyHCzJgS">Meese</persName>: but when we advance basing
                moved for <gloss target="#t_MX_1"><rs corresp="rec99k2btquR4fVXS" type="topic"
                        >MX</rs></gloss>, we must be prepared</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="receeGTv8IaT6tukJ">Haig</persName>: problem at moment is a <hi
                    rendition="simple_italic">political</hi> problem—getting on w/<gloss
                    target="#t_START_1">START</gloss> will resolve issue—<hi
                    rendition="simple_italic">if</hi> we raise issue now, it will complicate <gloss
                    target="#t_MX_1"><rs corresp="rec99k2btquR4fVXS" type="topic">MX</rs></gloss>
            </p>
            <p><persName corresp="recg0WDsRQgtuIKMw">Weinberger</persName>: ensure our budget
                planning</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="recWMTuTWgI0GTsmw">Inman</persName>: answer question (1) DELTA
                III testing—have to take out YANKEES—168? (2) at least 2 new <gloss
                    target="#t_ICBM_1"><rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic"
                    >ICBMS</rs></gloss> underway, can only test 1 (3) <rs
                    corresp="recbybjw3iHkqwwou" type="topic">BACKFIRE</rs> production less than it
                could be (4) <rs corresp="recAug8nb5QfVfzky" type="topic">SS–18</rs>
                <gloss target="#t_MIRV_1"><rs corresp="rec3jfDwQdQCBVT9H" type="topic"
                    >MIRVs</rs></gloss> (5) future <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic"
                    >verification</rs>—encryption of <rs corresp="recXyi0y36LV93Itc" type="topic"
                    >telemetry</rs></p>
            <p><persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName>: are they going ahead w/new
                sub programs</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="recWMTuTWgI0GTsmw">Inman</persName>:</p>
            <pb facs="0112" n="83" xml:id="pg_83"/>
            <p><persName corresp="recDfVAWTlyHCzJgS">Meese</persName>: I think we’re agreed (1) no
                [change] in public formulation (2) resist any attempt to revive <gloss
                    target="#t_SALT_1"><rs corresp="rec6OIA4luUvtBKNn" type="event"
                    >SALT</rs></gloss>
                <rs corresp="recF3SBVeQQW0d1aM" type="agreement-or-mandate">II</rs> (3) as a matter
                of policy, no constraints . . . when</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recM8U5HOaBRfTDmg">Rostow</persName>: don’t violate until deploy .
                . .</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec2p5eZ5kgeXCRJ4">McFarlane</persName>: we have words that
                capture this—<gloss target="#t_IG_1">IG</gloss>—get back to you</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recCAUUmNdxvAWExm">Rowny</persName>: whatever we say, distance
                ourselves from <gloss target="#t_SALT_1"><rs corresp="rec6OIA4luUvtBKNn"
                        type="event">SALT</rs></gloss>
                <rs corresp="recF3SBVeQQW0d1aM" type="agreement-or-mandate">II</rs>—help
                negotiate</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec2p5eZ5kgeXCRJ4">McFarlane</persName>: 2nd issue</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recg0WDsRQgtuIKMw">Weinberger</persName>: would hope paper not
                intended for dissemination—“some believe . . .”</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recMcElgnbOprdugv">Murphy</persName>: does this paper assume we’re
                satisfied w/ <rs corresp="recXyi0y36LV93Itc" type="topic">telemetry</rs> we’re
                getting now</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec2p5eZ5kgeXCRJ4">McFarlane</persName>: isn’t intended to—next
                issue mobiles—propose we reserve judgment in our position although <persName
                    corresp="recCAUUmNdxvAWExm">Rowny</persName> wishes to build in from start</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recCAUUmNdxvAWExm">Rowny</persName>: everyone’s agreed we want to
                keep open options re <gloss target="#t_MX_1"><rs corresp="rec99k2btquR4fVXS"
                        type="topic">MX</rs></gloss>—issue is <hi rendition="simple_italic"
                    >true</hi> mobile—if we don’t want, time to decide is now</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec2p5eZ5kgeXCRJ4">McFarlane</persName>: you have paper to
                consider—move on—do we want to ban heavies first, etc.—number of issues—to <gloss
                    target="#t_IG_1">IG</gloss>, w/ your approval, for report within two weeks</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recg0WDsRQgtuIKMw">Weinberger</persName>: I thought original paper
                did include banning of heavies</p>
            <p><persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Pres</persName>: <gloss target="#t_MX_1"
                    >MXs</gloss>?</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recg0WDsRQgtuIKMw">Weinberger</persName>: less than heavy</p>
            <p><persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Pres</persName>: Titans—trading chip?</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recs2P7y12AuR9gIG">Ikle</persName>: Soviets don’t worry about
                Titans</p>
            <p><persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Pres</persName>: heavier than <gloss
                    target="#t_MX_1"><rs corresp="rec99k2btquR4fVXS" type="topic"
                >MX</rs></gloss>?</p>
            <p>(chorus): 18s</p>
            <p><persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Pres</persName>: 18 heavier than 19?</p>
            <p>(chorus): yes</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recM8U5HOaBRfTDmg">Rostow</persName>: comment</p>
            <p><persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Pres</persName>.: if we go for heavier 1st,
                don’t we have negotiation problems</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recs2P7y12AuR9gIG">Ikle</persName>: it’s like
                SS-20/zero-option</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec4pU3LOkVX0BKPW">Hayward</persName>: get at 18s indirectly</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec2p5eZ5kgeXCRJ4">McFarlane</persName>: final
                issue—phasing—single or two agreements</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recg0WDsRQgtuIKMw">Weinberger</persName>: Phase <rs
                    corresp="recF3SBVeQQW0d1aM" type="agreement-or-mandate">II</rs> as important as
                Phase I—worried procedurally—would argue for <hi rendition="simple_italic"
                    >single</hi> treaty, <hi rendition="simple_italic">one</hi> process, because of
                strong importance we attach to <gloss target="#t_TW_1">TW</gloss> as only way to
                achieve equality at lower levels—if treaty w/ Phase I, doubt get them back</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="receeGTv8IaT6tukJ">Haig</persName>: thought this was issue you
                decided last time, Mr. <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Pres</persName>—if we
                can get objectives in I, sign Treaty—I read decision memo that <pb facs="0113"
                    n="84" xml:id="pg_84"/> way &amp; briefed on Hill, allies briefed that way—easy
                matter—have, for instance, 5 year review tied to good faith on Phase <rs
                    corresp="recF3SBVeQQW0d1aM" type="agreement-or-mandate">II</rs>—must keep
                credibility</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recg0WDsRQgtuIKMw">Weinberger</persName>: no one intends to
                undercut credibility</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="receeGTv8IaT6tukJ">Haig</persName>: must be clean or clear</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recg0WDsRQgtuIKMw">Weinberger</persName>: I’m worried—5 years/
                    <gloss target="#t_ALCM_1"><rs corresp="rec3r8I0hO6jAW3Fm" type="topic"
                        >ALCMs</rs></gloss> . . .</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="receeGTv8IaT6tukJ">Haig</persName>: if achieve everything in
                Phase I, then don’t sign, we’d be laughed out of court</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec4pU3LOkVX0BKPW">Hayward</persName>: if you get Phase I,
                substantial cut <gloss target="#t_TW_1">TW</gloss>
            </p>
            <p><persName corresp="recCAUUmNdxvAWExm">Rowny</persName>: <hi rendition="simple_italic"
                    >announcement</hi> of whether or not we seek agreement in Phase I should be kept
                open, from negotiating point of view (discuss Soviet tactics)</p>
            <p><persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Pres</persName>: when we talked about it, I
                didn’t think we meant 2 separate treaties—when we achieve 1st, then see what’s
                needed in phase <rs corresp="recF3SBVeQQW0d1aM" type="agreement-or-mandate">II</rs>,
                where we stand (asks question)—am I being Boy Scout</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="receeGTv8IaT6tukJ">Haig</persName>: you said it better than
                anybody</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec2p5eZ5kgeXCRJ4">McFarlane</persName>: will you sign</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recDfVAWTlyHCzJgS">Meese</persName>: can’t you reserve question
                until then</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="receeGTv8IaT6tukJ">Haig</persName>: it’s already been asked:
                    <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congress</orgName>, allies—don’t want to
                reverse decision already made, via this esoteric discussion</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recg0WDsRQgtuIKMw">Weinberger</persName>: don’t bind us because
                we’ve briefed w/o clarification of decision</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recM8U5HOaBRfTDmg">Rostow</persName>: explain as in <gloss
                    target="#t_INF_1">INF</gloss>, depends on how Soviets play it—don’t create
                impression we’re out to get one treaty quickly</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="receeGTv8IaT6tukJ">Haig</persName>: great danger is that it looks
                like you waffling on what you said: Phase I warheads—if bureaucracy’s confused, will
                emerge</p>
            <p><persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Pres</persName>: couldn’t part of negotiations
                be this</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="receeGTv8IaT6tukJ">Haig</persName>: yes, call it interim, or
                whatever</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recDfVAWTlyHCzJgS">Meese</persName>: Phase I—reserve decision</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec2p5eZ5kgeXCRJ4">McFarlane</persName>: precedent—conclude,</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="recjlYSNpDHCqlk6w">Bush</persName>: do we then go to Senate, ask
                ratify I?</p>
            <p>Ilke: do like test bans</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recg0WDsRQgtuIKMw">Weinberger</persName>: procedural matter—don’t
                tie hands by saying that once Phase I done, go to Senate</p>
            <p><persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Pres</persName>: until completed on Phase I,
                don’t know what <gloss target="#t_TW_1">TW</gloss> problem is in Phase <rs
                    corresp="recF3SBVeQQW0d1aM" type="agreement-or-mandate">II</rs></p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="receeGTv8IaT6tukJ">Haig</persName>: want to be careful of what
                has been bureaucratic hassle—don’t undercut Phase I unit of measure</p>
            <p><persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Pres</persName>: continuing negotiation</p>
            <p><persName corresp="recM8U5HOaBRfTDmg">Rostow</persName>: don’t fix on 2
                agreements</p>
